The paper deals with the computational complexity of a problem related to microarrays, which is a topic in bioinformatics. However, the paper focuses on the theoretical aspects of the problem and uses techniques from parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is closely related to parameterized complexity. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
